==옌도르의 부적 번제하기==

이 게임의 목표는 [[Astral Plane|아스트랄계]]에 있는 교차성향 [[high altar|주 제단]]에 [[Amulet of Yendor|옌도르의 아뮬렛]]을 바치는 것입니다. 이렇게 할 경우, 당신은 데미갓 일족으로 [[ascend|승천]]하게 됩니다.('필멸자여, 잘 하였도다!'). This does not take into account whether, or by what means, you have [[convert]]ed your alignment, so a [[helm of opposite alignment]] can be used to quickly ascend at a cross-aligned altar. However, you get a [[score]] multiplier of 2× if you never converted and are still of your starting alignment, or 1.5× if you converted and used a helm to change back.

If you offer the Amulet on a cross-aligned high altar, that altar's god gains dominion over yours and allows you to [[escape]] in celestial disgrace. If you offer the Amulet on the high altar to [[Moloch]] in the [[Sanctum]], Moloch 'mercilessly snuffs out your life', or if you have [[life saving]], disintegrates you into a pile of dust, ignoring disintegration resistance. (If you [[Explore mode|somehow]] survive that, you again escape.)

Offering a [[cheap plastic imitation of the Amulet of Yendor]] on a high altar gives a penalty of -1 luck and no other effect. However, if the amulet was ''identified'' as a fake, the penalty is instead -3 luck, -1 [[Alignment record|alignment]] and your god getting [[Anger|angry]] by 3.

Offering a real or fake Amulet on a non-high altar does not end the game. If the altar is an unaligned altar in [[Gehennom]], your god gets angry and Moloch [[smite]]s you. Otherwise, if hallucinating, 'You feel homesick'; or if the altar is co-aligned, 'You feel an urge to return to the surface'; otherwise, 'You feel ashamed'.

==자기 종족의 생명체 번제하기==
당신이 번제하는 생명체가 당신 자신의 종족일 경우 당신이 혼돈 성향이라면 좋은 효과가, 아니라면 나쁜 효과를 얻게 됩니다. 
해당 시체의 수명과는 관계가 없으므로, [[Zombie|좀비]]와 [[Mummy|미라]]도 제대로 작동할 것입니다.

;당신이 혼돈일 경우<nowiki>:</nowiki>
:당신은 성향 5 포인트를 얻게 됩니다.{{refsrc|pray.c|1219}}
:제단이 혼돈일 경우, 당신은 운 2 포인트를 얻습니다. 제단이 무성향일 경우, 당신은 운 2 포인트를 잃습니다.{{refsrc|pray.c|1197}} 해당 제단이 교차성향일 경우, 당신의 운은 영향받지 않습니다. (하지만 하단의 교차성향 제단 부분에 적혀있듯이, 해당 제단은 개종될 것입니다)
;당신이 혼돈이 아닐 경우<nowiki>:</nowiki>
:당신이 데몬으로 폴리모프하지 않았다면, [[wisdom|지혜]]가 혹사됩니다.{{refsrc|pray.c|1173}} ("당신은 이 악랄한 죄를 후회할 것이다!")
:당신은 성향 5 포인트를 잃게 됩니다.{{refsrc|pray.c|1214}}
:당신의 신의 분노가 3 증가합니다.{{refsrc|pray.c|1215}}
:당신의 운이 5 감소합니다.{{refsrc|pray.c|1218}}
:당신은 [[wisdom|지혜]] 1 포인트를 잃습니다.{{refsrc|pray.c|1216}} 이는 [[unicorn horn|유니콘 뿔]]로 치유될 수 있습니다.
:Outside of [[Gehennom]], your god will punish you as for [[pray]]ing too much (depending on the level of anger).{{refsrc|pray.c|1217}}
:If the altar ''is'' chaotic, you'll destroy it and anger any attendant priest.{{refsrc|pray.c|1188}}
;Whether or not you are chaotic<nowiki>:</nowiki>
:If the altar is chaotic or unaligned, a demon may be summoned. The demon will be [[peaceful]] if you are chaotic and hostile otherwise. The first two demons will be [[Juiblex]] and [[Yeenoghu]] in any order, followed by [[foocubi]].{{refsrc|pray.c|1203}}
:If you are polymorphed into a demon, "You find the idea very satisfying."; your [[wisdom]] is exercised.{{refsrc|pray.c|1170}}
:If the altar is lawful or neutral, it will immediately be converted to chaotic (except on the [[Astral Plane]]),{{refsrc|pray.c|1180}} independent of your alignment; if there is a [[aligned priest|priest]] tending the altar, they will be angered.{{refsrc|pray.c|1181}}

The check for same race is done before the check for a former pet and ignores the check for age, so same-race corpses are always fit for sacrifice until they rot away completely. This is just about the only time an undead creature is a valid sacrifice.

Keep in mind that [[werecreature]]s are considered [[Human (monster attribute)|human]], so sacrificing them if your character is human will have the consequences described above.

==애완동물 번제하기==
길들여진 상태에서 사망한 생명체를 번제하는 것{{refsrc|pray.c|1223}}은 일반적으로 당신의 성향치를 3 잃게 만들고{{refsrc|pray.c|1229}} [[aggravate monster|몬스터 자극]] [[intrinsic|본능]]을 얻으며 "So this is how you repay loyalty?"라는 메시지를 받습니다.{{refsrc|pray.c|1231}}. 애완동물은 &minus;1의 번제 가치를 가지므로,{{refsrc|pray.c|1230}} 이것은 해당 제단의 신이 [[anger|분노]]하는 결과만 불러올 것입니다.{{refsrc|pray.c|1335|name=negative_value|comment=negative-value sacrifice will anger the altar's god}}{{reffunc|pray.c|gods_upset|name=gods_upset}} 그 시체는 소모되지 ''않을'' 것입니다. Former pets that have [[tameness|gone feral]] no longer count as pets, and may be killed and sacrificed as usual.

==교차성향 제단들==
[[File:NHC-Altar-Conversion.png|thumb|(Level + 2) / (Level + 8)]]

당신은 교차성향 제단들에 번제함으로써 그것들을 변환시킬 수 있습니다.(하지만 주제단과{{refsrc|pray.c|1325}} [[Gehennom|게헨놈]]의 무성향 제단은 안 됩니다){{refsrc|pray.c|1343}}{{refsrc|pray.c|1346}} 실패할 경우 당신은 [[Luck|운]]을 1 잃고{{refsrc|pray.c|1406}}, [[wisdom|지혜]]를 혹사시킵니다.{{refsrc|pray.c|1407}} 성공할 경우 당신은 [[Luck|운]]을 1 얻고{{refsrc|pray.c|1384}}, 해당 제단은 교차성향이 됩니다. 캐릭터 레벨이 상승할 수록 변환시킬 확률도 증가합니다. [[aligned priest|해당 제단에 사제]]가 있는 채로 변환을 할 경우 그 사제가 당신을 공격하게 될 것입니다.{{refsrc|pray.c|1400}} 

제단을 변환시킬 확률은 당신의 경험치 레벨에 따릅니다; 확률은 <math>\textstyle\frac{level + 2}{level + 8}</math>입니다.{{refsrc|pray.c|1380}}

어떠한 경우에도, 제단을 보호하기 위해 [[minion|하수인]]들이 소환될 수도 있습니다.{{refsrc|pray.c|1398}}{{refsrc|pray.c|1410}}

제단을 변환하려고 시도할 때, 당신은 "''당신은 <당신의 신>''과 ''<제단의 신>'' 간의 대립을 감지한다."라는 메시지를 받게 될 것입니다.
변환이 성공할 경우 "당신은 ''<당신의 신>''의 힘이 상승하는 것을 느낀다."라는 메시지를, 실패할 경우 "불행히도, 당신은 ''<당신의 신>''의 힘이 감소하는 것을 느낀다."라는 메시지를 받게 될 것입니다.

'전' 애완동물과 같이 음수값을 가지는 번제물은 변환 시도를 발생시키지 않을 것입니다. 이것은 대신 해당 제단의 신을 분노하게 만들며, 실제로는 당신의 신의 분노를 1 ''감소''시킬 것입니다.<ref name="negative_value"/><ref name="gods_upset"/> You will still suffer the usual effects of angering a god, including the loss of any divine protection and being smitten by the angry god. The pet corpse is not consumed, so you can cure as much anger as you like.

{{anchor|altar_converts_you}}Attempting to convert an altar while your alignment is negative{{refsrc|pray.c|1346}} (or using a unicorn of your alignment; [[#Sacrificing unicorns|see below]] for details) may convert your alignment to that of the altar,{{refsrc|pray.c|1357}} take away 3 of your Luck{{refsrc|pray.c|1363}} and increase your prayer timeout by 300{{refsrc|pray.c|1364}} ("You have a sudden sense of a new direction"). Changing your alignment by any means resets your alignment record to zero.{{ref|httpsgithub.com/NetHack/NetHack/commit/3d1772a13b84e4643c8938010e4dca0931fa0406#diff-9e2fd3234ebdd323dee94c5cb5e8fdd3}}

This can only be done once per game on a non-unaligned altar;{{refsrc|pray.c|1347}} if this happens before you have been admitted to the quest, the game will be [[unwinnable]]. 

If you try to convert yourself a second time, or you sacrifice on unaligned altar in Gehennom, your sacrifice is rejected, you hear the voice "Suffer, infidel!", get &minus;5 to Luck,{{refsrc|pray.c|1371}} &minus;5 to alignment score,{{refsrc|pray.c|1368}} &minus;2 to wisdom,{{refsrc|pray.c|1372}} +3 to anger,{{refsrc|pray.c|1367}} and, unless in [[Gehennom]], you are punished by your current deity.{{refsrc|pray.c|1373}}

If you sacrifice on cross-aligned high altar, you don't convert it or yourself. Instead, you are attacked by the altar's deity.

As with coaligned altars, if you get a message saying "Nothing happens", then the corpse was too old and, indeed, nothing happened.

==유니콘 번제하기==
Sacrificing [[unicorn|유니콘]]s is complicated because the altar's alignment, your alignment, and the unicorn's alignment all factor into the outcome.{{refsrc|pray.c|1235}} A unicorn's alignment is represented by its color. The white is lawful, grey neutral, and black chaotic. The points to remember are:

* Never sacrifice a unicorn on an altar of its own alignment. You lose one point of [[wisdom]]{{refsrc|pray.c|1243}} and the altar's god becomes angry, with the [[Prayer#Possible negative effects of praying|same effect]] as angering that god through prayer.{{refsrc|pray.c|1244}}<ref name="negative_value"/> If the altar is not of your alignment, your god's anger is reduced by one.<ref name="gods_upset"/>
* Never sacrifice a unicorn of your own alignment (certainly not before you have completed the [[Quest]]). This acts as above if the altar is also of your alignment.{{refsrc|pray.c|1293|comment=<tt>unicalign == altaralign</tt> ist tested first}} If the altar is cross-aligned, this will set your alignment score to &minus;1,{{refsrc|pray.c|1257}} which makes your sacrifice convert ''you'' instead of the altar.
* Never sacrifice a unicorn on a [[Altar#High altars|high altar]]. On an altar of your own alignment, this is unnecessary. On an altar of another alignment, this will not convert you or the altar, but only angers the altar's god.{{refsrc|pray.c|1340|version=NetHack 3.6.0|comment=The "try to convert high altar" branch doesn't actually convert anything.}}

Each time you sacrifice a unicorn of a different alignment on your own altar, you get a +5 boost to your [[alignment record|alignment]]{{refsrc|pray.c|1251}} and the message "You feel appropriately {lawful | neutral | chaotic}",{{refsrc|pray.c|1249}} or "You feel you are thoroughly on the right path" if alignment is at maximum.{{refsrc|pray.c|1250}}

